(EMAPA:16291 "rhombomere 1 floor plate" (which is indirectly part of the metencephalon) is mapped to both UBERON:0003310 "floor plate of metencephalon" and UBERON:0005566 "rhombomere 1 floor plate", which is correct, but necessary only because UBERON:0005499 "rhombomere 1" is not part of UBERON:0001895 "metencephalon" in Uberon for this species. It would be better to add GCI part_of relations to rhombomeres and rhombomere floor plates, and to keep only the xref to UBERON:0005566 "rhombomere 1 floor plate".)

Should I add the GCI relationship? (same for EMAPA:16762 "4th branchial groove ectoderm", keep only xref to UBERON:0005662 "4th arch ectoderm", and add GCI relations to reach UBERON:0006846 surface groove, without needing the xref to UBERON:0005875 "4th arch pharyngeal cleft")

Should I add the GCI relationship? I guess this is because UBERON:0007186 is not part of "serous pericardium". Would be better to add a GCI relation and keep only the xref to UBERON:0007186.)

Should I add the GCI relationship? (EMAPA:32623 "forelimb skeleton" mapped to both UBERON:0010741 "bone of pectoral complex" and UBERON:0001440 "forelimb skeleton". Why UBERON:0010741? Need a GCI relation? Keep UBERON:0001440)

Should I add the GCI relationship? EMAPA:16033 "1-cell stage embryo": added xref to UBERON:0000106 "Zygote", which has synonym to ""1-cell stage" EXACT []" and ""one cell stage" EXACT []". Also UBERON:0000106 has "SeeAlso" relationship to  EMAPA:16033 "1-cell stage embryo" (Remove it now?).
CL:0000365 "Animal Zygote" had xref to EMAPA:16033 "1-cell stage embryo" in old onthology. Moreover is more animal specific (I guess)

EMAPA:16040 "compacted morula (mouse)": mapped to MmusDv:0000006 "Theiler stage 03" which is a stage defined as "embryonic cleavage stage defined by a dividing 4-16 cells egg, early to fully compacted morula". Seems more specific than mapping it to UBERON:0019248 "early embryo", ehich has xref to the more suited EMAPA:36032 "early embryo"

EMAPA:16064 "proamniotic cavity extraembryonic part (mouse)": mapped to UBERON:0012466 "extraembryonic cavities". Also may benefit from adding a relationship (part_of) to UBERON:0009742 "promaniotic cavity" which refers both to the intra- and extra-embryonic parts of the proamniotic cavity.

EMAPA:16071 "embryo mesoderm (mouse): mapped to UBERON:0000926 "mesoderm" which is defined as ""The middle germ layer of the embryo, between the endoderm and ectoderm.", so it is embryo specific. Not mouse specific though.

EMAPA:16077 "amniotic fold ectoderm (mouse)": mapped to UBERON:0004366 "extraembryonic ectoderm" because is a general feature that best suit the EMAPA term. It may benefit to link it with a part_of UBERON:0005971 "amniotic fold", or something similar.
EMAPA:16078 "amniotic fold mesoderm": mapped to UBERON:0005728 "extraembryonic mesoderm" for the same reasons than EMAPA:16077

EMAPA:16095 "future spinal cord neural plate (mouse)": mapped to UBERON:0003075 "neural plate" beacause is the most general feature that includes EMAPA:16095.  Also, UBERON:0003854 "spinal cord neural plate" has relationship to both UBERON:0006241 "future spinal cord" and UBERON:0003075 "neural plate", which links EMAPA:16095 with all the necessary anatomical features describing it.

EMAPA:16108 "allantois mesoderm (mouse)":  mapped to UBERON:0005728 "extraembryonic mesoderm" for the same reason than EMAPA:16078. Also, UBERON:0005728 "extraembryonic mesoderm" is_a UBERON:0004340 "allantois".

EMAPA:16120 "1st branchial groove ectoderm": 1st branchial groove ectoderm is synonym of "1st pharyngeal groove ectoderm" or "1st branchial cleft" ecc... All of these terms are synonyms of UBERON:0005872 "1st arch pharyngeal cleft". So, I chose to map EMAPA:16120 to UBERON:0005872

EMAPA:16123 "1st branchial membrane endoderm":  Mapped to UBERON:0009213 "pharyngeal membrane of 1st arch" for similar reasons as the line above. Maybe add relationship to UBERON:0004119 "endoderm-derived structure" and UBERON:0009722 "entire pharyngeal arch endoderm" which considers all the pharyngeal arches.

EMAPA:16126 "1st branchial arch ectoderm":  mapped to UBERON:0004362 "pharyngeal arch 1" for similar reasons as above.  Maybe add relationship to UBERON:0004121 "ectoderm-derived structure" and UBERON:0009722 "entire pharyngeal arch endoderm" which considers all the pharyngeal arches.

EMAPA:16127 "1st branchial arch endoderm": mapped to UBERON:0004362 "pharyngeal arch 1" for similar reasons as above. Maybe add relationship to UBERON:0004119 "endoderm-derived structure" and UBERON:0009722 "entire pharyngeal arch endoderm" which considers all the pharyngeal arches.

EMAPA:16136 "pericardio-peritoneal component mesothelium": mapped to UBERON:0007185 "pericardio-peritoneal canal mesothelium". Maybe it is more accurate to put a relationship part_to. But I'm not sure what "component" in the term-name refers to

EMAPA:16141 "future midbrain floor plate": mapped to UBERON:0007286 "presumptive floor plate", which I think is a synonym of "future floor plate" (maybe this should be added).
